              "action": "<p>\n St. Meinrad,\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=7650\">\n  martyr\n </a>\n is venerated as the patron and in some sense the founder of the Benedictine\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=19\">\n  abbey\n </a>\n of Einsiedeln in\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=11184\">\n  Switzerland\n </a>\n which has kept an unbroken continuity since Carolingian times. He settled as a hermit at Einsiedeln, where he was murdered by two ruffians to whom he had given\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=5904\">\n  hospitality\n </a>\n in 861. His\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  feast day\n </a>\n is January 21st.\n</p>\n",
