              "action": "<p>\n Benedictine abbess, the daughter of Blessed Pepin of Landen and Blessed Itta of Ida. Itta founded Nivelles\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=19\">\n  Abbey\n </a>\n and installed Gertrude as\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=18\">\n  abbess\n </a>\n in 639. Gertrude was a mystic, gifted with visions. She befriended the Irish saints Foillian and Ultan. Gertrude is a patroness of travelers and gardeners.\n</p>\n",
