              "action": "<p>\n Bishop of Tongres (in the modern Low Countries), best known for having been the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=5912\">\n  host\n </a>\n of\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=336\">\n  St. Athanasius\n </a>\n during the latters exile from his see of Alexandria, Egypt. He was probably an Armenian. Servatus was active at the Council of\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=10052\">\n  Rimini\n </a>\n in 359. He\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=9674\">\n  prophesied\n </a>\n the Hun invasion of\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=4817\">\n  France\n </a>\n in the mid-fifth century.\n</p>\n",
