              "action": "<p>\n St. Marcellus was elected Pope in 307, the last years of the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=9187\">\n  persecution\n </a>\n of the Church by Diocletian. He undertook the ecclesiastical reorganization of the Church and was most merciful to those who repented after having denied their Faith. When certain people known as the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=6858\">\n  Lapsi\n </a>\n refused to do\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/prayers/sacrament.php?id=4\">\n  penance\n </a>\n for their\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=930\">\n  apostasy\n </a>\n and thus were not pardoned by St. Marcellus, the tyrant Emperor Maxentius sent\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=726\">\n  St. Marcellus\n </a>\n into exile, where he died in 309 as a result of privations.\n</p>\n",
