              "id": 501,
              "action": "<p>\n Martyred king of Sweden, the author of the Code of Uppland or King Eric's Law. A devout Christian,\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=439\">\n  Eric\n </a>\n spread the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=4554\">\n  faith\n </a>\n through out the nation after his crowning in 1150. He campaigned against the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=8888\">\n  pagan\n </a>\n Finns and persuaded\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1918\">\n  Bishop\n </a>\n Henry of Uppsala, an Englishman, to remain in mis­sionary service in Finland.\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=439\">\n  Eric\n </a>\n was slain by Swedish nobles who were allies of Prince Magnus of Denmark. They beheaded him  near Uppsala as Magnus' any entered the region.\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=439\">\n  Eric\n </a>\n was never officially canonized but is patron of Sweden.\n</p>\n",
