              "id": 648,
              "action": "<p>\n Welsh bard who was is a popular patron in Brittany, France. Herve, sometimes called Harvey or Hervues, was the son of the bard Hyvarnion, and was born blind. Raised by his uncles because his mother was a hermitess, he was taken to Brittany. There he built an\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=19\">\n  abbey\n </a>\n at Lanhourneau, and he was venerated as a\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=8016\">\n  miracle\n </a>\n worker and bard. He is invoked against eye trouble, and he is depicted with a wolf. Tales and legends associated Herve with a wolf.\n</p>\n",
