              "action": "<p>\n A Benedictine\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=18\">\n  abbess\n </a>\n who was a gifted mystic. She had her first vision in 1152 and was known for ecstasies, prophecies, and diabolical visitations. She became\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=18\">\n  abbess\n </a>\n in 1157 .  Her cult was never formalized, but she is listed as a saint in the Roman Martyrology. Her brother, Ethbert, a Benedictine abbot, wrote her biography and recorded her\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=12111\">\n  visions\n </a>\n in three books.\n</p>\n",
