              "id": 717,
              "action": "<p>\n Ulric was born at Augsburg, Germany. He was educated at\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=650\">\n  St. Gall\n </a>\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=19\">\n  Abbey\n </a>\n in\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=11184\">\n  Switzerland\n </a>\n and by his uncle, St. Adalbeo,\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1918\">\n  bishop\n </a>\n of Augsburg. Ulric succeeded to the See as\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1918\">\n  bishop\n </a>\n in 923, and when\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1255\">\n  Augsburg\n </a>\n was plundered and ravaged by the Magyars, he led its inhabitants in the task of rebuilding the city and its cathedral. In his old age, he retired to St. Gall, named his nephew as his successor, and was accused of nepotism for his action. His canonization by Pope\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=1062\">\n  John XV\n </a>\n in 993 is the first recorded canonization by a Pope. His\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  feast day\n </a>\n is July 4th.\n</p>\n",
