              "action": "<p>\n Tarsicius was an acolite or perhaps a deacon at Rome. He was accosted and beaten to death on the Appian Way by a mob while carrying the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/prayers/sacrament.php?id=2\">\n  Eucharist\n </a>\n to some Christians in prison. The incident is included in\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=2550\">\n  Cardinal\n </a>\n Wiseman's novel \"Fabiola\", and Pope Damasus wrote a poem about it. Tarsicius is the patron of first communicants and his\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  feast day\n </a>\n is August 15\n</p>\n",
