              "action": "<p>\n Patroness of poor peasants and servants in the Tyrol. Born in Rattenberg, in the Tyrol, she was the daughter of peasants. At eighteen she became a servant in the household of Count Henry of Rattenberg When\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=8547\">\n  Notburga\n </a>\n repeatedly gave food to the poor, she was dismissed by Count Henry's wife, Ottilia, and took up a position as a servant to a humble farmer. Meanwhile, Henry suffering a run of misfortune and setbacks, wasted no\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=11571\">\n  time\n </a>\n restoring\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=8547\">\n  Notburga\n </a>\n to her post after his wife died.\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=8547\">\n  Notburga\n </a>\n remained his housekeeper for the rest of her life, and was famous for her miracles and concern for the poor.\n</p>\n",
