              "id": 975,
              "action": "<p>\n St. Ludmila was the daughter of a Slavic prince, she married Duke Borivoy of Bohemia, whom she followed into the Church. They built a church near\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=9565\">\n  Prague\n </a>\n and tried unsuccessfully to force\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=2927\">\n  Christianity\n </a>\n on their subjects. On the death of Borivoy, his sons Spytihinev and Ratislav, who had married Drahomira, succeeded him, and Ludmila brought up the latters son Venceslaus. On the death of Ratislav, Drahomira became regent, kept Wenceslaus from Ludmila and reportedly caused her to be strangled at Tetin. Her\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  Feastday\n </a>\n is September 16th.\n</p>\n",
