              "action": "<p>\n Widow and hermitess. She was born a peasant on February 6, 1347, in Montau, Prussia. After marrying a wealthy swordsmith, Albrecht of Danzig, Poland, she bore him nine\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/shopping/?category=28\">\n  children\n </a>\n and changed his gruff character. He even accompanied her on pilgrimages. However, when she went to\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=10148\">\n  Rome\n </a>\n in 1390, Albrecht remained at home and died during her absence. A year later Dorothy moved to Marienswerder, where she became a hermitess. She had\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=12111\">\n  visions\n </a>\n and spiritual gifts. Dorothy died on June 25 and is the patroness of Prussia. She was never formally canonized.\n</p>\n",
