              "action": "<p>\n Quentin was also known as Quintinus. According to legend, he was a Roman, went to Gaul as a missionary with\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=4324\">\n  St. Lucian\n </a>\n of Beauvais, and settled at Amiens in Picardy. He was so successful in preaching that he was imprisoned by prefect Rictiovarus, tortured, and then brought to\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1257\">\n  Augusta\n </a>\n Veromanduorum (Saint-Quentin), where he was again tortured and then was beheaded. His\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  feast day\n </a>\n is October 31st.\n</p>\n",
