              "action": "<p>\n Confessor and a patron of tailors and cloth workers. He was born in Cremona, Italy, where he became a merchant. Married, he was a model of\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=12106\">\n  virtue\n </a>\n beloved by all. Homobonus died on November 13 while attending\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/prayers/mass.php\">\n  Mass\n </a>\n at\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=121\">\n  St. Giles\n </a>\n Church in Cremona. His fellow citizens petitioned the\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=5849\">\n  Holy See\n </a>\n for his canonization, which was performed in 1199.\n</p>\n <p></p>",
