              "action": "<p>\n St. Colman of Cloyne -\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  Feast day\n </a>\n - November 24th He was born in Munster, Ireland, son of Lenin. He became a poet and later, royal bard at Cashel. He was baptized by\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=170\">\n  St. Brendan\n </a>\n when he was fifty years old with the name Colman. He was ordained, and was reputed to be St. Columba's teacher. He became the first\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1918\">\n  bishop\n </a>\n of Cloyne, of which he is patron, in eastern Cork.\n</p>\n",
