              "action": "<p>\n St. Flannan 7th. cent. bishop. Son of an Irish chieftain, Turlough he made a pilgrimage to\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=10148\">\n  Rome\n </a>\n where Pope\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=1047\">\n  John IV\n </a>\n consecrated him. On his return he became first\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=1918\">\n  bishop\n </a>\n of\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/encyclopedia/view.php?id=6642\">\n  Killaloe\n </a>\n and also preached in the Hebrides. His\n <a href=\"https://www.catholic.org/saints/f_day/\">\n  feast day\n </a>\n is December 18th.\n</p>\n",
